		"description": "<p>Scissors and thread act as if they were a magic wand in your grip, turning mere cloth into works of art. You gain proficiency with weaver&rsquo;s tools, or if you are already proficient you gain an expertise die instead. You can use your weaver&rsquo;s tools to turn similar clothing into specific outfits (for example turning noble&rsquo;s clothes into an admiral&rsquo;s uniform, or turning commoner&rsquo;s clothes into a replica of a specific commoner&rsquo;s outfit). Converting outfits in this way takes you 10 minutes worth of work and the Perception and Investigation check DC required to notice your handiwork is equal to your passive Intelligence weaver&rsquo;s tools score. In addition, you have advantage on checks made to create schematics for cloaks and other cloth items.</p>",
